Immediately create an Inventory Committee to conduct a physical count/inventory of the PPE and supplies which shall be witnessed by the auditor and submit to the audit team the Report of the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RCPPE) and Report of the Physical Count of Inventories (RCPI); and

Direct the Municipal Treasurer to maintain Property Cards and the OIC-Municipal Accountant to maintain PPE Ledger Cards and to ensure that the balances in quantity per PC always reconcile with the Ledger Cards and the control accounts in the General Ledger;  

Evaluate personnel workloads to handle the abovementioned additional responsibilities.

(b) We have recommended the following:


Management to immediately create an Inventory Committee to conduct an inventory of the local roads under the jurisdiction of the Municipality and to render a Report on the Physical count of the Road Networks System;

