Management commented that most of the KKK Loan recipients were already dead. As for the Advances to Contractors, they are not sure if these refer to mobilization fee granted to contractors since there are no available records which pertain to the said account. Nevertheless, the management committed to comply with the audit recommendations.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor being the Chairman of the Local School Board to:
Convene earlier with the LSB for the timely review and approval of the SEF Budget to avoid delays in the implementation of the PPAs under the said fund;
Direct the Municipal Budget Officer to assist the LSB in reviewing SEF budget particularly in the coming up with a more specific and detailed PPAs for appropriation;
Instruct the Bid and Awards Committee to properly plan and schedule all procurement activities pertaining to educational projects for their timely implementation; and
Direct the Municipal Accountant to review claims and their supporting documents before effecting payment.
The Municipal Budget Officer agreed to comply with the audit recommendation. She guaranteed to call the attention of the Board to convene earlier for the timely review of the Budget.

We have recommended that the ICO-Municipal Accountant:

Trace unreconciled balances from previous years of Due From and Due To Other Funds accounts amounting P2,728,015.20 and P1,561,784.73, respectively;

Make the necessary adjustments in the book of accounts based on the table presented above to reflect the correct balances of the affected accounts;

Transfer the actual cash to the specific fund where it really belongs, if necessary, to avoid accumulation of balances; and

Conduct regular reconciliation of the accounts to ensure that the balances of reciprocal accounts are the same at all times.

We have recommended to the Local Chief Executive to activate and mobilize its WATSAN council to:
Prepare a reasonable work plan for the consideration of the Sanggunian Bayan in the provision of annual funding for the operations and maintenance of the water systems;
Assist the DAWASA through provision of capacity building activities on how to operate and maintain the system so that it can sustain its operations in the long run;
Exercise its policy and management oversight function over DAWASA; and
Address the issues and concerns for the newly completed Cambaly water system.

We have recommended that the Municipal Treasurer:

Continue to demand settlement of tax liabilities from the identified taxpayers;

Document the main reasons why these remained uncollected for the past years;

Adopt corresponding strategies to address the specific concerns of the taxpayers; and

In coordination with the Provincial Treasury Office, avail of the administrative and legal remedies provided by law to enforce collection of the delinquent real property taxes.

